This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and machine translation. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves training models using an algorithm. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing models that can learn and make decisions. It may also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves identifying alignments between words and phrases. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.DL (Deep Learning) as it involves training models using a Viterbi EM algorithm.
